# Fake News Detector

A machine learning web application that detects whether a news article is real or fake using NLP techniques and deep learning. Built as a portfolio project to demonstrate end-to-end ML development from data preprocessing to production deployment.

**Live Demo:** [mafake-news-detector-app.streamlit.app](https://mafake-news-detector-app.streamlit.app)

---

## Overview

This project trains and compares two text classification models on the [Kaggle Fake and Real News Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/clmentbisaillon/fake-and-real-news-dataset) (~45,000 articles). Users can paste an article, enter a URL, or upload a CSV to get instant predictions with confidence scores.

---

## Features

- **Single Model Prediction** — classify any article using either model with confidence score and TF-IDF term breakdown
- **Model Comparison Tab** — run the same article through both models side by side with an agreement indicator
- **URL Scraping** — paste any news URL and the app extracts the article automatically
- **Batch Prediction** — upload a CSV of articles and download results
- **Adjustable Threshold** — tune the classification sensitivity via a sidebar slider

---

## Models

### Logistic Regression + TF-IDF
- 50,000 features with unigrams and bigrams
- Sublinear TF scaling and English stop word removal
- Fast inference — results in under 1 second
- ~99% accuracy on test set

### DistilBERT (Fine-tuned)
- Pre-trained `distilbert-base-uncased` fine-tuned for 3 epochs
- Understands context and word relationships unlike bag-of-words approaches
- Hosted on [Hugging Face Hub](https://huggingface.co/MA00100/fake-news-distilbert)
- ~99.4% accuracy on test set

| Model | Accuracy | ROC-AUC |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Logistic Regression | ~99.0% | ~0.99 |
| DistilBERT | ~99.4% | ~0.999 |

---

## NLP Pipeline

```
Raw Text
    ↓
Preprocessing
    ├─ Lowercase
    ├─ Remove URLs and mentions
    ├─ Remove punctuation and digits
    └─ Collapse whitespace
    ↓
TF-IDF Vectorizer          DistilBERT Tokenizer
    ├─ 50,000 features          ├─ WordPiece tokenization
    ├─ Bigrams                  ├─ 512 token limit
    └─ Sublinear TF             └─ Attention mask
    ↓                           ↓
Logistic Regression        DistilBERT Classifier
    ↓                           ↓
        Probability Score (0-1)
```

