## Project Structure

```
fake-news-detector/
├── app.py               # Streamlit web application
├── train_model.py       # TF-IDF + Logistic Regression training
├── train_bert.py        # DistilBERT fine-tuning
├── eda.py               # Exploratory data analysis
├── requirements.txt
├── True.csv             # Real news articles (Kaggle)
└── Fake.csv             # Fake news articles (Kaggle)
```

---

## Local Setup

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/MA0610/Fake-news-detector-app.git
cd Fake-news-detector-app
```

### 2. Create a virtual environment
```bash
conda create -n news-env python=3.11
conda activate news-env
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Download the dataset
Download `True.csv` and `Fake.csv` from [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/clmentbisaillon/fake-and-real-news-dataset) and place them in the project root.

### 4. Train the models
```bash
# Train Logistic Regression (~1 minute)
python train_model.py

# Fine-tune DistilBERT (~20 min with GPU, ~5 hours CPU)
python train_bert.py
```

### 5. Run the app
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## Dataset

| File | Articles | Label |
|------|----------|-------|
| True.csv | 21,417 | Real (1) |
| Fake.csv | 23,481 | Fake (0) |

Articles cover political news from 2015–2018. The dataset is well-balanced making it suitable for binary classification without class weighting adjustments.

---

## Key Design Decisions

**Why DistilBERT over full BERT?** DistilBERT is 40% smaller and 60% faster while retaining 97% of BERT's performance — a better tradeoff for a deployed web app where inference speed matters.

**Why keep Logistic Regression?** It demonstrates understanding of classical ML tradeoffs. On this dataset LR achieves near-identical accuracy to BERT at a fraction of the compute cost, which is worth knowing as a practitioner.

**Why Hugging Face Hub for model hosting?** The fine-tuned model is 255MB — too large for GitHub. Hugging Face Hub provides free model hosting with automatic versioning and the `from_pretrained()` API loads it in one line.

---

## Potential Improvements

- LIME or SHAP explainability to highlight influential words in predictions
- Add LIAR or GossipCop dataset for better generalization
- FastAPI backend to expose model as a REST API
- Prediction history tracking across sessions
- Model performance metrics dashboard

